{
  "texts": [
    "Now, the deformation datum is defined in [Moc25, §3.4.2] (see also [Moc25, §2.3.4]) as",
    "(Here, we consider I slightly enlarged on the right, so that I ∂ ∩ W actually includes θ 0.)",
    "It is not too difficult to see that, by the construction of ν given above, this corresponds to the desired morphism (4), since for any U ∈ A, the other components of ν •φ -1 (V 0 ⟨f ⟩ | I | U) give no other contribution to the component V 0 ⟨g⟩ | J | W due to the fact that the overlap of any such U with J contains a Stokes direction of the pair (f U, g).",
    "This completes the proof for the case J ∂ > I ∂.",
    "Let us now indicate the proof for the other case, when I ∂ > J ∂."
  ]
}